column1:
[{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'The teams are on their way out, it should be a decent affair this and West Indies might actually have a chance of winning for once! Sheldon Cottrell to open the bowling...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '5.50pm We got there in the end. No Marchant de Lange for the host which is perhaps surprising - maybe because they have selected two allrounders in Parnell and Wiese.'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Almost time for the toss, the captains are coming out in very hot conditions - beautiful day in Cape Town. Pitch looks solid but perhaps a little grass, one across from the Test wicket. South Africa have won the toss and will bat, interesting to see the teams...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'South Africa 1 Morne van Wyk, 2 Reeza Hendricks, 3 Rilee Roussow, 4 Faf du Plessis (capt), 5 David Miller, 6 Farhaan Behardien, 7 David Wiese, 8 Wayne Parnell, 9 Kyle Abbott, 10 Kagiso Rabada, 11 Imran Tahir'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Just waiting for the West Indies XI. The one we've been given has Dwayne Bravo in it, the same Bravo who is supposedly currently in Australia. All sorts of confusion but it does appear the Bravo has boarded a plane and is set to play here..."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'West Indies 1 Chris Gayle, 2 Dwyane Smith, 3 Marlon Samuels, 4 Dwayne Bravo, 5 Kieron Pollard, 6 Denesh D Ramdin, 7 Darren Sammy, 8 Andre Russell, 9 Jason Holder, 10 Ashley Nurse, 11 Sheldon Cottrell'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "5.15pm Afternoon folks and welcome to the first T20 from Cape Town. In the context of the cricket to come this is an odd series that doesn't really fit, but it represents West Indies' best chance of success on this tour. They have a strong looking squad while South Africa have rested a few players, although still have plenty of talent. Toss and teams coming in just over ten minutes."}]
column56: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Russell comes back after a terrible first over...'}]
column63: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "G'day everyone, lovely to see you in the sunshine. Quite even, this, so far"}]
column69: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Ah, DJ Bravo, time to make a point or two, perhaps'}]
column75: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'The captain, Darren Sammy, brings himself on in place of Nurse now'}]
column90: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Ramdin up to the stumps, trying to box Miller in now'}]
column93: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Russell back into the attack'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '"Not sure not taking Pollard to the World Cup will be all that big a loss," observes Sundar. "He has not exactly lived up to his reputation, which frankly was based on his T20 exploits"'}]
column99: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Immediate chance for Cottrell to make amends as he is thrown the ball'}]
column102: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Farhaan Behardien is in at No. 6 but the batsmen crossed'}]
column106: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Bravo back into the attack with three overs to go'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Here\'s GermanPlayer: "Even if Miller had scored a century today, I still think he is a big problem that will result in our loss in the WC. We\'d be better off taking a specialist middle order batsman instead of him. When was the last time he played an innings of note in T20 or ODIs?"'}]
column118: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Final shuffle from Sammy, it will be Cottrell to bowl out. SA looking about par, I'd say"}]
column124: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Welcome back for the chase, you always back the West Indies in T20 with their power. Kyle Abbot to open the bowling...'}]
column154: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Last over of the Powerplay, this has been brutal stuff so far for the hosts. Wayne Parnell on now...'}]
column160: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'A rather well trimmed Imran Tahir into the attack...'}]
column215: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Just 19 to win now. Not sure what Parnell can do...'}]
column221: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Tahir back, can South Africa take another with them here...'}]
column239: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "What a meal they've made of this chase, how has it lasted until the final over! Pretty dull T20 the last seven overs or so. Wiese needs a miracle..."}]
column240: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "So it does need Sammy to finish it off. Well he's off strike so probably not..."}]

column1: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length at the body, turned down to long leg'}]
column2: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fuller length, swings back into the thigh pad of the right-hander, beating his attempted press to leg'}]
column3: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'shorter, too straight and whipped over deep-backward square leg, what timing, fast hands, pulled away, nailed'}]
column4: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "shortish again, outside off now, lucky for the bowler it's only cut to backward point"}]
column5: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'better, pitched up a foot outside off and left alone'}]
column6: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'goes to pull a ball on a length, misses, struck on the thigh pad too high for an lbw appeal'}]
column7: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pulled from outside off, gets an under-edge but it lands well short of the wicketkeeper'}]
column8: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'similar ball, this time cut without timing but gets it through the covers'}]
column9: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fuller length, two-feet outside off, left alone'}]
column10: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tighter line, now nudged out towards backward point'}]
column11: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'this leaves the right-hander who follows it and plays and misses, it zips through and carries to head height, nice to see'}]
column12: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'touch fuller, reached out for and pressed to backward point'}]
column13: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length on the off stump, punched from the crease to extra-cover'}]
column14: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length angled in, pulled smartly backward of square and gets it away from the deep square for four, very nicely steered away'}]
column15: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'touch shorter and this is just dropped into midwicket for an easy single'}]
column16: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'touch fuller and a touch wider, driven over the top off the back foot, timed pretty well and extra-cover has to be sharpish to save the boundary'}]
column17: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'awful ball, short and wide, cut through cover, well timed'}]
column18: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on the stumps, forward dropping this into midwicket for a sharp single'}]
column19: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length just outside off, dabbed down to backward point'}]
column20: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fuller length, a touch wider, van Wyk tried to run it down to third man and missed'}]
column21: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'straighter line and tucked backward of square leg for an easy single'}]
column23: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tucks this in front of square and they can get a single here'}]
column24: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length on off stump, played forward with an open face, gets it down to third man'}]
column25: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'swing into the right-hander who pokes at it, gets a thick bottom edge that bounces and loops over Ramdin for a boundary'}]
column26: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full, swings into the pads and out lbw! Lovely delivery, classic left-armer's dismissal. Nice full length and the inswing did for the batsman who almost fell over. Would have cannoned middle and leg"}]
column27: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'another decent delivery, kept out to midwicket this time'}]
column28: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pushed across the right-hander and two wide outside off'}]
column29: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full down the leg side, clipped to long leg's right"}]
column30: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full again, this is a low full tossed tucked to midwicket'}]
column31: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length, pulled at and missed, done for pace, it ripped through'}]
column32: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full just outside off, tried to run it down to third man but gets an edge and taken at slip! Straightforward catch well taken by Chris Gayle and West Indies bag another. Again, the batsman perhaps beaten for pace and got a healthy edge straight to slip'}]
column33: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full length just outside off, pressed straight to cover'}]
column34: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tighter line, driven well but straight to mid-on this time'}]
column35: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'similar ball, angled face wide of cover for a sharp single, batsman has to dive in but got in comfortably enough'}]
column36: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'steps across the stumps to work leg side, they turn down the second with deep square charging in'}]
column37: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball a foot outside of, bit of a slap down the ground only finds mid-on'}]
column38: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full length, pressed back up the bowler'}]
column39: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'wider line, square driven but only to cover point'}]
column40: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'touch shorter, batsman across his stumps flicking through midwicket, no second on'}]
column41: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'around the wicket, full on the stumps, pressed down to long-on'}]
column42: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full but wide of off stump allowing du Plessis to have a swing at it, gets it out to deep cover'}]
column43: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on the stumps, single flicked down to long-on once more'}]
column44: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a lenght just outside off, tried to advance down before pulling, thick bottom edge to the right of Ramdin for a quick single'}]
column45: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'down the track and lifts a length ball down the ground, got enough on it, well over mid-on, quite a controlled stroke, timed it well'}]
column46: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'short of a length, blocked on off stump up on his toes'}]
column47: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "hangs back in the crease before hacking a length ball from the off stump wide of long-on who's now back on the fence, bit of a heave but effective"}]
column48: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'yorker, dug out back to the bowler'}]
column49: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'great shot, very full again but not quite the yorker and du Plessis drives it past mid-off, timed it so well, raced over the outfield'}]
column50: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'forward on the off stump, pressed into the covers'}]
column52: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "down the track and lifted really well straight down the ground, that's the shorter of the straight boundaries on this ground"}]
column53: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'a little short and pulled hard onto the grass banks over midwicket'}]
column54: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'forward to a full ball just outside off, flicked out through midwicket, just a single because the fielder is there in a hurry'}]
column55: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fraction outside off, cut out to deep cover'}]
column56: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "length a foot outside off, pushed off the back foot down to long-on, they come back for the second and a direct hit would have beaten the batsman's dive at the striker's end"}]
column57: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'slips down leg despite a caught-behind appeal'}]
column58: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'off stump line, length ball, tried to be launched into the leg side but only gets a mishit down to long-on'}]
column59: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full length just outside off, driven well down the ground, straight to mid-off but through his fingers! The fielder was well in from the rope, had he been back it was an easy take, still got there with a leap but couldn't cling on"}]
column60: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length on the stumps, pulled powerfully away and finds the gap wide of midwicket'}]
column61: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full toss on the stumps, tried to be flicked leg side but gets a big leading edge that's taken by mid-on! A real bonus wicket, poor ball really but du Plessis totally miscued it and it presented a simple chance for Sammy"}]
column63: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'angled in with the arm, straightening a touch and tapped into the covers'}]
column64: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "dragged down on the leg side and Rossouw tries to work off his pads, rolls towards short midwicket and despite Ramdin's quick feet they pick up one"}]
column65: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fired on the stumps, deflected away behind square for another leg bye'}]
column66: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "pushed through towards leg stump and Rossouw attempts to reverse-paddle, gets a thin under-edge and it beats Ramdin, scuttles away to the boundary - not quite where it was intended to go but he'll take the result"}]
column67: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'moves his line outside off, Rossouw stays back and slaps one through the covers to the sweeper'}]
column68: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'flighted on the stumps, goes down on one knee and sweeps another single'}]
column69: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'starts around off stump and Miller punches one down the ground to long-off'}]
column70: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "slower ball, outside off stump and Rossouw can't time it off the back foot, steers it to backward point"}]
column71: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'goes around the wicket, cutting his fingers over the ball, Rossouw is down the wicket and skelps a couple on the drive to wide long-off'}]
column72: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'shortens his length, hacks across the line and an inside edge runs to backward square but they manage to steal one more'}]
column73: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pitched up in the channel, Miller uses the feet, punches a single towards long-off'}]
column74: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Rossouw tries to get cute, sets himself early for a reverse flick but completely misses another slower ball that sails wide of off stump'}]
column75: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'short and on leg stump, Miller could put this where he likes but his pull picks out backward square leg and is only good for one'}]
column76: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball around off stump, comes down the pitch and drives to long-off'}]
column77: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pitched up, maybe a touch slower, nicely timed off the pads to deep midwicket'}]
column78: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'taking the pace off again, in the channel outside off, punched forcefully into the covers'}]
column79: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full and straight, neatly flicked off the pads, behind square but not that much pace and there's a man on the ropes to cut it off"}]
column80: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pushed across the left-hander from over the wicket, driven towards deep extra cover and they get back for two again'}]
column81: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball, too straight from Bravo and it sits up for Rossouw to club across the line, picks the gap for a welcome boundary, first in a few overs'}]
column82: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "slower-ball bouncer, furious swing of the arms but this time it's much closer to the man in the deep"}]
column83: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball on middle and leg, worked off the pads and they do well to pinch a second off Russell running in'}]
column84: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'good length, 130kph on the stumps, Miller whips it to deep midwicket'}]
column85: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'makes an early move to reverse the ball through the off side, then changes his mind and deflects one more off the legs'}]
column86: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full and wide of the stumps, cracked square but Sammy gets a diving hand on it, takes the pace off and keeps them to one'}]
column87: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'on the stumps, worked away for a couple more with a turn of the wrists'}]
column88: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Sammy drops short and Miller wallops this off the front foot out towards deep midwicket, Russell is slow to pick it up and then can't do much more than grasp thin air as the ball whistles past him. Tough to call it a drop but was definitely a chance"}]
column89: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full and straight, punched back just where it came from... and straight into the non-striker's stumps. No rewards for that beautifully timed stroke"}]
column90: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'pushed through outside off, played back on the off side for a single'}]
column91: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tight line, tries to run a single away behind square off an open face but finds short third man'}]
column92: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'drops a little short, Rossouw backs away and clubs through the off side, long-off runs around to keep them to two'}]
column93: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "angled across and Miller slaps the ball hard to point, Sammy can't take it cleanly but still prevents a run"}]
column94: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'overpitched, Miller crumps a low full toss through the covers, wide of the sweeper and they get two'}]
column95: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full and straight, comes forward and punches towards deep midwicket'}]
column96: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "that's the delivery Russell is aiming for, hitting that wide yorker length, dug out towards long-off for one"}]
column97: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'goes short and at the batsman this time, mistimed pull comes off the bottom edge into the off side'}]
column98: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full on leg stump, Rossouw ramps it towards short fine leg where Cottrell fails to cling on, that's a drop, not the most straightforward but he got down to it and then shelled the chance, poor hands"}]
column99: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tries a wide slower ball but this is misdirected, outside the tramlines'}]
column100: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length delivery, another cutter, slashed through the covers from outside off'}]
column101: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'got him, full length outside off, Miller tries to scoop it over extra cover but the bat turns in his hands and he picks out the man standing on the boundary. Bit of a soft dismissal when you know what Miller can do to that sort of ball'}]
column102: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'good delivery, not quite yorker length but well directed, Rossouw gets lucky with a thik inside edge that goes fine of the fielder on the edge of the ring'}]
column103: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'takes the pace off, loopy full delivery, Rossouw waits on it and bunts a couple back past the bowler'}]
column104: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full and straight, punched back along the ground and Cottrell fields'}]
column105: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'slower ball on the stumps and Rossouw is waiting, makes Cottrell pay again for that drop, plants the front foot and belabours this wide of long-on for four more'}]
column106: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'rolls his fingers over this, outside off stump, pushed through the covers'}]
column107: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'high arc on this slower ball, outside leg stump and Rossouw nearly mistimes his flick, floats safely wide of short fine leg for one'}]
column108: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "touch short, pushed square from the crease and an attempt to hit the stumps at the striker's end results in a second for Behardien"}]
column109: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length outside off, rides the bounce and steers one more towards point'}]
column110: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full and in the slot outside off, Rossouw judges it perfectly and slams four down the ground, clean pick up and swing through the line'}]
column111: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full length, wobbled out on off stump, can't get under this but still worth a couple as long-off has to come scrambling in off the fence"}]
column112: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'starts with a genuine bouncer, Behardien ducks and it is adjudged okay on height'}]
column113: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length delivery outside off, goes at it hard and gets one via an inside edge'}]
column114: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on off stump, Rossouw clumps one through the off side - 150 up for SA, worth some choons for the crowd'}]
column115: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'woof, how has that missed?! Excellent slower ball from Russell, the batsman lost all shape trying to heave it out of the ground but the ball bounced just over the top of the stumps'}]
column116: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "full and straight, smashed back, Russell goes tumbling after it and the ball deflects towards midwicket off the non-striker's wicket, they hare back for two"}]
column117: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'picks the slower ball and puts a few air miles into this! Lovely timing from Behardien, down on one knee and lofts this elegantly into the stands at deep extra cover'}]
column118: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'starts with a full toss, must have been perilously close to a no-ball, Rossouw hoicks it into the leg side and picks up the single that takes him to a well-paced 50'}]
column119: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'goes around the wicket to the right-hander, attempted yorker in the channel and Behardien can only squeeze a single through point'}]
column120: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'up in the blockhole again from Cottrell, backs away and clubbed hard along the ground to long-on for one more'}]
column121: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'around the wicket, another full toss, pulled towards long-on, the bottom hand coming off the bat and they immediately set off for two, Russell needed a direct hit but was nowhere near'}]
column122: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'slightly back of a length, coming in with the arm and Behardien is beaten for pace - well bowled'}]
column123: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full and straight, manages to dig this out into the leg side, Russell chugs across from long-on to clean up and that is an excellent final over from Cottrell'}]
column124: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'poked at from the crease on off stump, thick outside edge down to third man'}]
column125: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'crunching drive, half-saved at extra-cover, absolutely nailed that Gayle'}]
column126: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on the stump, blocked up to mid-on'}]
column127: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'forward press from off stump into a gap between extra-cover and mid-off'}]
column128: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'back of a length at the body, tucked down to square leg'}]
column129: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball swings back a little and strikes the pad, huge cry for lbw, not out, probably just outside the line, maybe high too'}]
column130: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'bit of a hack from just outside off, thick inside edge down to long leg'}]
column131: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full sliding across the left hander, slides away a little, beats him'}]
column132: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length on a much straighter line, tucked into mid-on'}]
column133: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'bumper, hooked at and misses, it bounces very high and over the keeper'}]
column134: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full just outside off and crunched over long-on, trademark Gayle, big whack, in the slot for him really, such a clean strike'}]
column135: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'step to leg and this time takes a length ball over straight midwicket, absolutely creamed it once again'}]
column136: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length on a middle and off line, knocked back up the wicket'}]
column137: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'touch straight and steered past short long leg with a roll of the wrists'}]
column138: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'bumper, it gets up just enough and Smith ducks'}]
column139: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fuller angled in, blocked into the covers'}]
column140: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "swept around the corner again, can't be too straight to Smith"}]
column141: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'a step down the wicket, frees the arms and strokes a length ball over long-off, superb, the timing perfect once more'}]
column142: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full angled at the pads, Smith misses aiming a flick leg side'}]
column143: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'finds the gap at midwicket with a little push forward'}]
column144: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'low full toss on off stump, Gayle was aiming leg side but gets a thick outside edge past backward point'}]
column145: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'moves to the leg side, the bowler tries to follow him but to no avail, blasted away from middle and leg over long-off'}]
column146: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'whacks it leg side this time, clean as a whistle, it screams past mid-on'}]
column147: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "short ball, Gayle tries to whack it somewhere and gets a bit of a top edge into the off side, cover charges back and dives but can't get there"}]
column148: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on the pad, pushed back to the bowler'}]
column149: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length ball a foot wide of off stump, Smith stays leg side of it and blasts it past mid-off, great timing, fifty up already'}]
column150: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'tightens the line and this is just blocked'}]
column151: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': "touch shorter and Smith farms it over midwicket, stand and whack, that's how you earn your money in this format"}]
column152: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'wide outside off, Smith can only find point'}]
column153: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'fuller and much straighter, clipped to the left of short long leg and Tahir dives to save well'}]
column154: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'full on the off stump, driven at, it swings in to take a thick inside edge that runs very fine, lucky for the batsman'}]
column155: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'wider line and angled out to third man'}]
column156: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'length outside off, pulled hard over mid-on, more of a club this time but still enough meat'}]

column123: [{'type': 'HTML', 'html': '7.30pm: So, West Indies have been set 166 to win on what is a slightly slow Newlands pitch. Apparently, that score is above par for T20s on this ground, but we\'ll see whether the stats can handle the boys in maroon shortly. Smit, for one, has done the maths differently: "I would argue if its a par total, Alan, that with Gayle, Pollard, Bravo, Smith and Sammy... this is still below par!!" Find out with Alex in 15.'}]

[{'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'So the Gayle-force blows in to Cape Town. Will he travel up to the Wanderers on Sunday? 1pm start. Join us then...'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "Presentation time. I wonder who might be Man of the Match? Oh yes, it's Chris Gayle, the fastest fifty for the West Indies. 11 balls for 52 runs in the middle of his innings, incredible stuff today."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'Here\'s Faf du Plessis: "It\'s a captain\'s nightmare. Tough for the bowler but a real learning curve for them. He\'s done that to every attack in the world. If you don\'t get him out he\'s going to hurt you. We had a small opportunity with a catch just out of Rilee\'s reach and you have to take those. I thought we posted a really good total, average at Newlands is about 150. We brought it back well at the end but we were just on the end of Chris Gayle today."'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "West Indies got on top with the ball quite quickly with regular wickets and it took Rilee Rossouw to ensure the hosts had a solid total to bowl at but nothing was big enough for Gayle in today's mood. He bludgeoned the ball to all parts and having flown in a few days ago, he's blasted his side to a first win on this tour. Amazing how the short format brings out the best in the West Indies. They're one-up in this three-match series."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': 'And Darren Sammy: "We were determined to make up for the Test series. This is a format we\'re very confident with. The beauty of our team is the power hitters. It was hard to pick the XI. But we\'re going to play free and fearless, sometime it may look sloppy but that\'s the way we\'re going to play. Chris gives himself a chance, sees what the wicket does and then it\'s helter-skelter. But also, Jason Holder bowled well up front but we didn\'t start or finish out overs well enough - the first and last balls we conceded too many boundaries."'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': "The chase fizzed out remarkably and West Indies have won by four wickets but in reality this has been a hammering. Chris Gayle produced a real special, we don't often get it nowadays on the international stage but today he was brilliant and destroyed the South Africans. When he got out, West Indies slightly laboured but still got home with plenty in hand, even if they did take almost all the time available to them."}, {'type': 'HTML', 'html': '

'}]
